At least 20 initiates have died in the Eastern Cape since the start of the summer initiation season. For more, eNCA speaks to Contralesa, Kgoshi Mathupa Mokoena. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - At least 20 initiates have died in the Eastern Cape since the start of the summer initiation season. READ: Concern over illegal initiation schools The causes of death include dehydration, underlying health co-morbidities, and diabetes. Most of those who died this season are from the OR Tambo region of the Eastern Cape.